<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1127">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.001 C23/7</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 510</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 26, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that, in
                            compliance with the Department’s instruction number 285 of August 31,
                            1917, I have to-day placed in the hands of President Carranza, President
                            Wilson’s acknowledgment of the letter whereby President Carranza
                            announced his assumption of the office of President of the United
                            Mexican States.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry P. Fletcher</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>